      "comment": "PATH TO VICTORY (6) finished out of the money on debut two starts back then he was always well out of his ground and was beaten 3.5 lengths when fifth over 1607m at Stawell two weeks ago. With those runs under the belt, and the modest nature of this contest, he looks hard to beat. BRUTALRULE (2) is a nine-start maiden who finished sixth at his most recent appearance over 1600m at Swan Hill but might be poised to return to something like the good form of last prep after three runs back, the latest over this trip. ZIP EMPATHY (7) is a first-starter who has struck the right race to make an impression on debut going off a solid second placing at the latest jumpout, which was over 1300m. LUCKY CRIMSON (5) led early before tiring to finish eighth over 1307m at Stawell but should be nearing peak fitness now. DEADLY DEVIL (3) got back into the placings last start, albeit beaten a long way, but draws well and looks ready for 1600m.",
